race.comment: UNDERRATED (3) is in the top stable and brings a win and near miss to peak, both heavily bet. Has some weight relief and a fancied stablemate has been scratched. HÃ©'s clearly the one to beat. BOOM CRUSHER (5) won his Maiden three starts back and has gone close at his last two runs, most recently when second over 1200m at Mackay. Is a winner at this circuit and tumbling in weight must be respected. UNIVERSAL HARMONY (2) resumes and performs fresh. He's been competing in stronger and will be wound up to give a big sight. SPELLMASTER (6) needs to lift a lot to be winning but can fill out the first four in the depleted field.
